text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: And so the originalist rationale cited
by the court is really an attempt to
justify the continued dominance of
the socio-political elite at that time.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: Exactly Mr. Rabbit! Exactly.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: It's a powerful idea Mr. Rabbit.
And one likely lost upon your
peers, so allow me to repeat it.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: What Mr. Rabbit is saying is that the
struggle over a scarce supply of carrots
brings out the worst in rabbitkind.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: And that absent a government
monopoly, the life of a rabbit
would be solitary, poor ...

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: ... nasty, brutish, and short.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: And therefore--

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: Wait, what? That's the exact
opposite of what I was saying.

text.title: Professor Cal V. Hobbes
text.tspan: Mr. Rabbit, you are an idiot.
Cite as: Andrew Fong, Nasty, Brutish, and Short, TORT BUNNIES (January 24, 2011), http://tortbunnies.com/78.html.
